<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12015g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12015g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12015g"> 15(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Olivier Basselin / Vaux-de-Vire / vaudeville</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>Olivier Basselin</mark>, the poet, who collected and arranged the satirical songs known as <mark>Vaux-de-Vire</mark>, and which have given rise, it is said, to the expression <mark>vaudeville</mark>, was born in the valley of the Vire; and the house in which he was born is in the <i>Vux-de-Vire</i>, near the village of Martilly, about a mile from Vire. <small> <a name="COOK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#COOK"><cite title="source">Cook's Traveler's Handbook for Normandy &amp; Brittany</cite></a> (1923) 125</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
